</p>


                            <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';"><br><b>2)Motivation is a continuous process.</b>
<br>Some words might be expressions for you, but maybe they can help in making this world a better place to live. Be the change that you wish to see in the world.
<br>⦁	Motivate people, but most importantly “Stay motivated yourself”.
<br>⦁	Find motivation in those little things that you do every day, every moment, in every bit of your life.
<br>⦁	From taking birth to breathing continuously- every single moment till you die;
<br>⦁	From waking up to going back to sleep
<br>⦁	From childhood to old- age
<br>⦁	From Teenage to Adulthood
<br>⦁	From being a child to being a parent
<br>⦁	From life to death, motivation lies in everything.
<br>⦁	It lies within you. Spread it to the universe as much as possible.

<br><br><a href="https://www.cio.com/article/3194546/4-key-techniques-for-continuous-improvement-in-corporate-innovation.html">Source</a>


<br><br><b>3)Motivation may be positive or negative.</b>
<br>When on the death bed, when you know it is the time. You pray and wish to do. Why?
<br>Why will someone grant such a wish for themselves?
<br>But there is the motivation behind dying too, getting rid of all the physical pain that you might experience which can make conditions worse for you. So, one feels better to die than to suffer on the death bed.
<br>There is a motivation behind everything in life.  
<br>One’s survival is not possible without motivation. One can live without food for some days, but it’s impossible to live without motivation.

<br><br><b>4)Motivation may be internal or external.</b>
<br>There is motivation in every little thing, from an ant to an elephant, from a seed to a tree, from an infant to a grown-up, from cradle to death bed.

<br>You might not be able to see the motivation at times, but remember no matter how big problems are, there is always hope, and behind this hope, you’ll always find a ray of motivation.
<br>As surveyed, the presence of a corporate incentive program motivated 66% of employees to stay at their job. A 5% increase in employee retention can generate a 25% to 85% increase in profitability.
<br><br></p>
